### In Poland and Lithuania

Voivodeships played a crucial role in the administrative structure of the [Polish–Lithuanian Commonwealth](/Polish%E2%80%93Lithuanian_Commonwealth) (1569–1795), as well as in later Polish states. Below is a detailed breakdown of voivodeships across different historical periods.

#### Polish–Lithuanian Commonwealth (1569–1795)

The Polish–Lithuanian Commonwealth was divided into numerous voivodeships, each with its own regional governance. These were categorized into three main regions:

1. **Polish Crown Lands**:
   - [Poznań Voivodeship](/Pozna%C5%84_Voivodeship_(14th_century_%E2%80%93_1793))
   - [Kalisz Voivodeship](/Kalisz_Voivodeship_(1314%E2%80%931793))
   - [Gniezno Voivodeship](/Gniezno_Voivodeship)
   - [Sieradz Voivodeship](/Sieradz_Voivodeship_(1339%E2%80%931793))
   - [Łęczyca Voivodeship](/%C5%81%C4%99czyca_Voivodeship)
   - [Brześć Kujawski Voivodeship](/Brze%C5%9B%C4%87_Kujawski_Voivodeship)
   - [Inowrocław Voivodeship](/Inowroc%C5%82aw_Voivodeship)
   - [Chełmno Voivodeship](/Che%C5%82mno_Voivodeship)
   - [Malbork Voivodeship](/Malbork_Voivodeship)
   - [Pomeranian Voivodeship](/Pomeranian_Voivodeship_(1466%E2%80%931772))
   - [Płock Voivodeship](/P%C5%82ock_Voivodeship_(1495%E2%80%931793))
   - [Rawa Voivodeship](/Rawa_Voivodeship)
   - [Masovian Voivodeship](/Masovian_Voivodeship_(1526%E2%80%931795))
   - [Kraków Voivodeship](/Krak%C3%B3w_Voivodeship_(14th_century_%E2%80%93_1795))
   - [Sandomierz Voivodeship](/Sandomierz_Voivodeship)
   - [Lublin Voivodeship](/Lublin_Voivodeship_(1474%E2%80%931795))
   - [Podlaskie Voivodeship](/Podlaskie_Voivodeship_(1513%E2%80%931795))
   - [Ruthenian Voivodeship](/Ruthenian_Voivodeship) (later [Chełm Voivodeship](/Che%C5%82m_Land) after 1772)
   - [Bełz Voivodeship](/Be%C5%82z_Voivodeship)
   - [Volhynian Voivodeship](/Volhynian_Voivodeship_(1569%E2%80%931795))
   - [Podolian Voivodeship](/Podolian_Voivodeship)
