## Modern Voivodeships of Poland (1999–Present)

Following a major administrative reform in 1999, Poland's voivodeships were consolidated into **16 larger provinces**, each with its own regional assembly (*sejmik*) and elected governor (*marszałek*). These modern voivodeships are:

1. [Lower Silesian Voivodeship](/Lower_Silesian_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Dolnośląskie*)
2. [Kuyavian-Pomeranian Voivodeship](/Kuyavian-Pomeranian_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Kujawsko-Pomorskie*)
3. [Lublin Voivodeship](/Lublin_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Lubelskie*)
4. [Lubusz Voivodeship](/Lubusz_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Lubuskie*)
5. [Łódź Voivodeship](/%C5%81%C3%B3d%C5%BA_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Łódzkie*)
6. [Lesser Poland Voivodeship](/Lesser_Poland_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Małopolskie*)
7. [Masovian Voivodeship](/Masovian_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Mazowieckie*)
8. [Opole Voivodeship](/Opole_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Opolskie*)
9. [Subcarpathian Voivodeship](/Subcarpathian_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Podkarpackie*)
10. [Podlaskie Voivodeship](/Podlaskie_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Podlaskie*)
11. [Pomeranian Voivodeship](/Pomeranian_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Pomorskie*)
12. [Silesian Voivodeship](/Silesian_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Śląskie*)
13. [Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship](/%C5%9Awietokrzyskie_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Świętokrzyskie*)
14. [Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship](/Warmian-Masurian_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Warmińsko-Mazurskie*)
15. [Greater Poland Voivodeship](/Greater_Poland_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Wielkopolskie*)
16. [West Pomeranian Voivodeship](/West_Pomeranian_Voivodeship) (*Województwo Zachodniopomorskie*)

Each voivodeship is further subdivided into *powiaty* (counties) and *gminy* (municipalities), forming a three-tiered system of local governance.

